{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":177199,"duration_api_ms":204353,"num_turns":27,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"4c72c410-fb93-4ac1-b6c8-9bd5dc61a8f6","total_cost_usd":1.05104705,"usage":{"input_tokens":20,"cache_creation_input_tokens":46751,"cache_read_input_tokens":870837,"output_tokens":4435,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":46751,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":20,"outputTokens":4435,"cacheReadInputTokens":870837,"cacheCreationInputTokens":46751,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.83858725,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":188,"outputTokens":8408,"cacheReadInputTokens":967093,"cacheCreationInputTokens":58818,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.21245979999999998,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Reviewed the diff across src/adapters/fs.rs and src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs (2 files, ~225 lines changed). All three issues from the project prompt are addressed:\n\n**Issue 1 (journal detail structs):** Fully resolved in a prior round — fs.rs imports and reuses `StartJournalDetails` and `CompletionJournalDetails` from model.rs. No duplicate structs remain. Both use `#[serde(default)]` on optional fields (no `deny_unknown_fields`). Merge logic is field-by-field with explicit conflict rules.\n\n**Issue 2 (runless-to-named completion):** The diff correctly converts `unique_terminal_replay_match` from returning `Option<usize>` to `AppResult<Option<usize>>`, replacing the previous `tracing::error` + return `None` with a proper runtime error for the `(Some(run_id), None)` contract violation — satisfying the requirement to replace debug_assert-style guards. The new fall-through path at the `[open_index] if run_id.is_none()` match arm correctly attempts terminal replay matching instead of immediately erroring when started_at doesn't match the open runless row. New test `terminal_replay_falls_through_past_mismatched_open_runless_row` covers this scenario.\n\n**Issue 3 (plan_hash auto-populate):** Fully implemented with `snapshot_plan_hash` and `safe_plan_hash_backfill` functions. Backfill-only semantics (never overwrites existing), terminal replay explicitly excluded, plan evolution detected via `snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation` provenance field.\n\nAll 683 tests pass. No `debug_assert!` guards remain in changed files. No `deny_unknown_fields` anywhere.\n\nThe changes are correct, safe, and well-scoped.","amendments":[{"body":"In `unique_terminal_replay_match`, the `AppError::CorruptRecord` error uses `file: \"unique_terminal_replay_match\"` (a function name) rather than a file path. All other `CorruptRecord` errors in fs.rs use actual file paths like `milestones/{id}/task-runs.ndjson`. This should use the task-runs.ndjson path for consistency and to help operators locate the problematic file. The caller has `milestone_id` available and could pass it in, or the function could accept it as a parameter.","rationale":"When this error surfaces in logs or user-facing output, `file: \"unique_terminal_replay_match\"` gives no indication of which file is corrupt, making debugging harder. Every other CorruptRecord in the file points to a real path. This is a minor but real diagnostic gap — not cosmetic."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"71b98ab5-21ef-4f14-a605-d2bba44d0b5f"}
